The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Feb. 16: ITC Ltd will build three super deluxe luxury hotels in Chennai, Bangalore and Hyderabad at a cost of Rs 1,000 crore. ?These hotels would be functional in the next two to three years,? ITC chairman Y. C. Deveshwar said on the sidelines of a CII function here today. At present, ITC runs 66 hotels across 50 countries.

 New Delhi, Feb. 16: The empowered group of ministers on restructuring of Delhi and Mumbai airports is likely to meet in a couple of days to finalise the request for proposal documents, which would outline the requirements of modernising the airports for the bidders.

 New Delhi, Feb. 16: Indian Oil Corporation (IOC) plans to import about 0.7 million tonnes of ultra low sulfur petrol and diesel in February and March to meet the April 1 deadline for supply of green fuels in the country. 

 New Delhi, Feb. 16: Oriental Bank of Commerce is set to carry out a major manpower restructuring, especially at the acquired Global Trust Bank unit, after it gets a report from National Institute of Bank Management.

 New Delhi, Feb. 16: The domestic personal computer (PC) market grew 32 per cent year-on-year in 2004 to 3.43 million units, according to analyst firm IDC.




